# Piano Player Mode - Hand Guide Overlay

Add a translucent hand overlay that highlights fingers to guide users through songs.

## Design

- **Hand image** overlaid on camera feed (translucent)
- **Song selector** dropdown to choose from available songs
- **Finger mapping**: C=Pinky, D=Ring, E=Middle, F=Index, G=Thumb (left hand), A-B (right hand)
- **Playback** shows which finger to press next

## Proposed Changes

### [MODIFY] [piano-player.html](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/airplay%202/piano-player.html)

1. Add song selector dropdown with all 5 songs
2. Add hand overlay container with finger highlighting zones  
3. Add Start/Stop playback controls
4. JavaScript to:
   - Fetch and parse music TXT files
   - Step through notes with timing
   - Highlight corresponding fingers using CSS classes

### [NEW] Copy hand image to `airplay 2/hands.png`

## Note-to-Finger Mapping

| Note | Hand | Finger |
|------|------|--------|
| C | Left | Pinky |
| D | Left | Ring |
| E | Left | Middle |
| F | Left | Index |
| G | Left | Thumb |
| A | Right | Thumb |
| B | Right | Index |

## Verification

Manual test: Select song, click Start, verify fingers highlight in sequence.
